@startuml
title Communication Flow - Asynchronous (Event-Driven)

participant "Order Service" as ORDER
participant "Message Broker\n(Kafka/RabbitMQ)" as BROKER
participant "Payment Service" as PAYMENT
participant "Notification Service" as NOTIF
participant "Analytics Service" as ANALYTICS
participant "Payment DB" as DB_PAY
participant "Order DB" as DB_ORDER

== Creación de Orden ==
ORDER ->> ORDER: Crear orden
ORDER ->> DB_ORDER: Persistir orden
activate DB_ORDER
DB_ORDER -->> ORDER: Order ID: 12345
deactivate DB_ORDER

ORDER ->> BROKER: [1] Publicar evento\nOrderCreated {orderId: 12345, userId: 789}
activate BROKER
note right of BROKER
  Topic: "orders.created"
  Partition: hash(userId)
  Retention: 7 días
end note

== Consumidores suscritos ==
BROKER ->> PAYMENT: [2] Consume evento
activate PAYMENT
PAYMENT ->> PAYMENT: Crear transacción de pago
PAYMENT ->> DB_PAY: Registrar pago pendiente
activate DB_PAY
DB_PAY -->> PAYMENT: Done
deactivate DB_PAY

par Procesamiento paralelo
  PAYMENT ->> BROKER: [3a] PaymentProcessed
  note right of BROKER
    Topic: "payments.processed"
  end note
  
  BROKER ->> NOTIF: [3b] Consume PaymentProcessed
  activate NOTIF
  NOTIF ->> NOTIF: Enviar email "Pago recibido"
  NOTIF ->> NOTIF: Enviar notificación push
  NOTIF ->> BROKER: [4] NotificationSent
  deactivate NOTIF
  
  BROKER ->> ANALYTICS: [3c] Consume OrderCreated
  activate ANALYTICS
  ANALYTICS ->> ANALYTICS: Registrar métrica
  ANALYTICS ->> ANALYTICS: Actualizar dashboard
  deactivate ANALYTICS
  
  BROKER ->> ORDER: [3d] Consume PaymentProcessed
  activate ORDER
  ORDER ->> DB_ORDER: Actualizar estado orden
  activate DB_ORDER
  DB_ORDER -->> ORDER: Done
  deactivate DB_ORDER
  ORDER ->> BROKER: [5] OrderConfirmed
  deactivate ORDER
end

deactivate PAYMENT
deactivate BROKER

note bottom
  **Advantages of Event-Driven pattern:**
  ✓ Fully decoupled services
  ✓ Parallel processing
  ✓ Independent scalability
  ✓ Resilience: if a service fails events persist
  ✓ Event sourcing: full history
  ✓ Easy to add new consumers
  ✓ Delivery guarantees: at-least-once
  
  **Ordering guarantees:**
  • Partitioned by userId
  • Order guaranteed within a partition
  • Idempotent consumers
end note

@enduml
